1. Need an Admin capability to Create/Update/Delete/Search Employees

instructionsIfAny:
1. Click on the IDE button will open an IDE in a different window.

2. The skeleton Maven project is already pre-created by the system to give you a head start.

3. You can include any third party Maven libraries in to your pom xml as you wish.

4. Write test cases or sql scipts to write data into the Mysql.

5. If you are done for the day and wish to continue the next day - run the data scripts or the test case to enter data into the system. Our MySQL containers are at present virtual and stateless to make sure we have a limited database foot print.

6. You can continue to see you code across multiple development sessions.

7. The environment configured had a in build Tomcat and a MySQL instance. Check out the i/p and port details for the servers access by referring the accompanying image.

8. For your information - the system spawns 2 container boxes - one for development called dev-machine and other for MySQL called - db. Your code and the web server(Tomcat) gets deployed into dev-machine, while the database works from db.

9. For every new session, the port info of servers may change. In order to know the Tomcat port, go to Machines console, right click on dev-machine and click on Servers to see the I/P - Port info similar to the accompanied image. Do the same to check out the port of your database.

10. Once you are through with your assignment, click on 'Submit my Workspace' button. The reviewer will be notified by email having a link to your code base.

11. There are automation's, triggered by your click, to verify the quality of your code. Entire code quality report is dispatched to the reviewer who may then do functional validation of your app..
